         <abstract id="aspace_190d29989c6bad4e40370434464817ea">This collection consists of material related to a two volume set of <title>
               <part>Jankyn's Book of Wikked Wyves</part>
            </title>, edited by Ralph Hanna III and Traugott Lawler as part of the Modern Language Association's Chaucer Library Series. In the first volume, Hanna and Lawler presented comprehensive versions of the three medieval texts that comprised Jankyn's "Book of Wikked Wives" which is referenced in "The Wife of Bath's Tale" in <title>
               <part>The Canterbury Tales</part>
            </title>. In the second volume, Hanna and Lawler presented the known contemporary commentaries on one of the three texts, Walter Map's "Dissuasio Valerii," or "The Letter of Valerius to His Friend Ruffinus, Dissuading Him from Marrying." The bulk of the material consists of transcriptions, translations, glosses and reproductions of portions of the commentaries, which were used during the production of volume two. It includes some material not in the published work. The collection also includes drafts of volume one and correspondence related to the project.</abstract>
         <langmaterial id="aspace_7ee29b3325531c9d2b8ba01663d9c57a">
            <language>The materials are in English, Latin,  and Middle English (1100-1500).</language>
         </langmaterial>
